Subject: [PATCH 06/10] event: temporarily disable verbose logs

Because stderr of event handlers is directly printed to the console,
this will pollute output when using e.g. 'buildhistory' which calls a
shell function.

Patch disables 'set -x' temporarily while executing the event handler.

Signed-off-by: Enrico Scholz <enrico.scholz@sigma-chemnitz.de>
---
 lib/bb/event.py | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/lib/bb/event.py b/lib/bb/event.py
index a5f026e..a4afc39 100644
--- a/lib/bb/event.py
+++ b/lib/bb/event.py
@@ -80,7 +80,9 @@ def execute_handler(name, handler, event, d):
     if 'd' not in builtins:
         builtins['d'] = d
         addedd = True
+    old_verbose = bb.msg.loggerVerboseLogs
     try:
+        bb.msg.loggerVerboseLogs = False
         ret = handler(event)
     except (bb.parse.SkipRecipe, bb.BBHandledException):
         raise
@@ -94,6 +96,7 @@ def execute_handler(name, handler, event, d):
             logger.error("Execution of event handler '%s' failed" % name)
         raise
     finally:
+        bb.msg.loggerVerboseLogs = old_verbose
         del event.data
         if addedd:
             del builtins['d']
